React js

 - if you are using react in browser so we can install react-dom package.
 - If you are using react in mobile so we can install react native package.

 - We can install react app two way or other way
    - This is first way react offical doc:- npx create-react-app projectname
    - This is second way using Vite website:- npm create vite@latest -> choose react -> choose Javascript or typescript

 - React official website install - So we can code write any .js file or .jsx file
                                  - But function name should be capital like eg. Chai not chai
                                  - In this project, the react-scripts package is mandatory. It automatically calls the index.js file located in the src folder. The index.js file renders the app into the element with the ID ‘root’, which is defined in the index.html file inside the public folder. There is no need to call it directly, as react-scripts handles this automatically.
                                  - In that way unnecessary package install which is no need to you can check in package.json file.

 - React using Vite build tool  - So we can code write only .jsx file
                                - Function name should be capital and file name also should be capital like eg Chai not chai
                                - In that way only necessary pacakge install like React and React-dom package
                                - In Vite, there is no need for the react-scripts package. The application is directly loaded through the index.html file, which is outside the src folder. In this file, the main.js file is included using a <script> tag. You can rename the main.js file as per your convenience.

