Virtual Dom- VD is lightweight copy of the real dom. it is update only the change parts of the UI instead of updating whole page.thats why its faster

Real DOM- Document object model - it is actul structure of web page in the browser when any changes happen it updates whole DOM, thats why its slow as compare virtual dom

React fiber- React fiber is internally reconcilation engine. it makes ui updates faster by breaking another work into small task. They decide which task need to priortiy and which task to pause all thing decide to react fiber. and react fiber introduct in after react js 16

Virtual DOM and Fiber- Virtual dom decide what to update and react fiber decide how and when to update it

What is JSX- JSX is javascript xml. it is looks like html it is easy to wirte and read code. 
Why not javascript code-  Because javascript code is complex and less readable as compare to jsx.

UseCallBack(): return memorized function. it means suppose if you function that function call in your child component but parent component call any state or any function call that tiem unnecessary call that method so that case avoid for useCallBack() hooks

useMemo() return memorized value. if you function in that function has complex logic but suppose we changed some other functionality so unneccessayy that function call so that case for avoiding so we need to use useMemo hooks 

memo(): it is use for unnecessary re rendering of component when its props do not change value. so that time we can use

<a></a> Is it use A tag in react -> No becuase a tag is refresh page so thats why no need to use a tag you can use Link tag for react dom

context - In context file we should create .js file not jsx
     
